  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5617",
  "title": "🐛 Pagination doesn't get the correct page when use routing after relodad",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nAfter navigate with the pagination, for example to the page 2, and reload the page the pagination will show the page 1  instead of page 2 that is the truly page that is requested (when use routing with Next)\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. In the index click in \"[Go to the brand Samsung](https://hnivvj-3000.csb.app/brands/samsung)\"\r\n2. Click in the page 2 https://hnivvj-3000.csb.app/brands/samsung?instant_search%5Bpage%5D=2\r\n3. Refresh the page\r\n4. You will see the page 1 as active but the URL show the page two as active\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/algolia-next-static-get-server-state-bug-hnivvj\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nWhen a url contains the active page, this is the one that should be displayed\n\n### Package version\n\neact-instantsearch-hooks-web: 6.41.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nmacOS 13.3.1\n\n### Browser\n\nFirefox 112.0.2\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
